Defendant Quentin Dory Ferguson in court with Attorney Cheryl Anne Ward.  Defendant Quentin Dory Ferguson in custody.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Matter here for sentencing.   Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.

The Court imposed the following sentence:   AS TO COUNT #1:  The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be THIRTY-EIGHT (38) months.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for FOURTEEN (14) months with credit for 373 days time served.  Defendant shall serve TWENTY-FOUR (24) months on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  

The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program;
The defendant is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
  
The Court advised the defendant of the determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Randsom urine screens to ensure compliance;
 - Seek and maintain full-time employment and/or schooling at least 40 hours a week;
 - No contact with Rayshawn Williams or Daren Hayes;
  - Pay the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements.  Court ordered monies taken by the Department of Correction from up to 25% of prison funds.  The balance would then be paid while on extended supervision.  If not paid, will convert to a civil judgment.   

